TUSCOLA WIND II, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Tuscola Wind II, LLC ("Tuscola II") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Tuscola Wind II generating facility ("Tuscola II Facility").
Tuscola II is a wind turbine generating facility located in Tuscola County, Michigan. The Tuscola II Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by International Transmission Company, LLC and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Tuscola II's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Tuscola II Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Tuscola II's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Tuscola II shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $437,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $36,416.66.
